Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 10/10] wifi: mt76: mt7921: add runtime-verification harness

Add a comprehensive runtime-verification framework for the mt7921u
USB driver.  This is a source-level only patch that provides debug
traces, debugfs trigger files, and test scripts for human testers
to verify the bug fixes from patches 0001-0008.

4.1  Dynamic debug traces:
 - mcu.c: dev_dbg() in mt7921_mcu_set_clc() and __mt7921_mcu_set_clc()
   showing alpha2, env_cap, idx before the for loop / command send
 - mcu.c: dev_dbg() in mt7921_mcu_parse_response() showing cmd id and
   status on MCU response receipt
 - usb.c: dev_dbg() in mt7921u_mcu_send_message() showing cmd id on
   MCU command send entry
 - mac.c: dev_dbg() in mt7921_mac_wtbl_update() showing idx and mask
 - mt792x_core.c: dev_dbg() in mt792x_roc_timer() on ROC timer fire
 - main.c: dev_dbg() in mt7921_roc_work() at entry/exit

4.2  debugfs trigger files (test_trigger_debugfs.c):
 Five read-only trigger files under .../mt76/test_trigger/, all
 protected by module parameter test_trigger_enable (default 0):
  - trigger_testmode_null: verify BUG-01 (NULL drv_own on USB)
  - trigger_wtbl_poll: verify BUG-02 (WTBL poll timeout)
  - trigger_mcu_retry: verify BUG-03 (MCU command retry)
  - trigger_clc_load: verify CLC regulatory / fallback
  - trigger_roc_timer: verify BUG-04 (ROC timer state)

4.3  Test scripts (testing/):
 Seven individual scripts (T1-T7) plus a master orchestrator:
  - test_t1_testmode.sh: testmode NULL deref verification
  - test_t2_wtbl.sh: WTBL poll timeout verification
  - test_t3_mcu_retry.sh: MCU command retry verification
  - test_t4_clc.sh: CLC regulatory verification
  - test_t5_suspend.sh: suspend/resume verification
  - test_t6_reset.sh: queue wake on reset verification
  - test_t7_twt.sh: TWT functionality verification
  - test_harness.sh: master orchestrator with --test, --interface,
    --log-dir arguments

All test scripts output standardised [PASS]/[FAIL]/[SKIP] results and
capture dmesg and trace output to a log file.

Signed-off-by: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
---
